glossary.activeFrame: 'The value listed here is what frame the attack hitbox will come out when the attack is performed.Ex.If the value is 10-12, then the attack hitbox will be active from frames 10-12.
glossary.cancel: CCan be canceled by a special move, Drive Impact, Drive Rush or Super ArtSACan only be canceled by a Super ArtSA2Can only be canceled by a level 2 or 3 Super ArtSA3Can only be canceled by a level 3 Super Art or Critical Art*Can only be canceled by specific attacks
glossary.comboScaling: In addition to the regular combo scaling, any unique scaling that an attack has is displayed hereInitial ScalingScaling added when the first hit of the combo landsCombo ScalingScaling added after the second hit of the combo landsImmediate ScalingScaling added to the attack itself after the second hit of the combo landsMultiplier Scaling Scaling value that is multiplied by subsequent combo scaling values when incorporated into a combo.
glossary.hitDriveGaugeIncrease: Amount of Drive Gauge recovered by the attacker when the attack hits
glossary.blockDriveGaugeDecrease: Amount of Drive Gauge lost by the defender when blocking
glossary.punishCounterDriveGaugeDecrease: Amount of Drive Gauge lost by the defender on a Punish Counter
glossary.properties: Displays the attack hitbox properties.HHigh level attacks that can be blocked standing or crouchingMMid level overhead attacks that must be blocked standingLLow level attacks that must be blocked crouchingTThrows that cannot be blockedPProjectile attacksMPMid-air projectile attacks that are considered to be aerial attacks

rows.miscellaneous: Perfect Parry activates when an attack is absorbed on the frame a parry is input, or on the next frame. (For high and overhead attacks, the player must press the direction away from the opponent. For low attacks, down and back)If no direction is inputted the result will be a regular parry with an additional Drive increase of 3000.Fully invincible for 5 frames once recovery is over (invincibility not granted if you continue the parry)The player on the receiving end of a Perfect Parry cannot cancel and is forced into a Punish Counter state until their move is finished
